      • markAbstractStructure

        protected void markAbstractStructure(StructureType type,
                                     StructureUsage usage,
                                     java.util.Collection<StructureType> structureTypesToCheck)
        Updates referrers and/or warns for undefined structures based on references to an abstract StructureType: a reference type that may refer to one of a number of defined structure types passed in structureTypesToCheck.

        For example using Cisco devices, see CiscoStructureType.ACCESS_LIST and how it expands to a list containing many types of IPv4 and IPv6 access lists.

      • markConcreteStructure

        protected void markConcreteStructure(StructureType type,
                                     StructureUsage... usages)
        Updates referrers and/or warns for undefined structures based on references to then given StructureType. Compared to markAbstractStructure(org.batfish.vendor.StructureType, org.batfish.vendor.StructureUsage, java.util.Collection<org.batfish.vendor.StructureType>), this function is used when the reference type and the structure type are guaranteed to match.
